<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/27.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">Scholle</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your October 1. Informally discuss with the President of Cuba the
                            proposed Amnesty Bill, and, should he seem inclined to approve the act,
                            point out to him the view of this Government that if the act should
                            become law it would create an unfortunate impression that crimes against
                            person and reputation are allowed to go without adequate punishment in
                            Cuba. Make clear to the President that <pb facs="0304" n="188" xml:id="pg_188"/> the above suggestion arises from the friendly
                            interest taken by the Government of the United States in matters
                            affecting Cuba’s standing before the world.</p>
                        <p>See previous instructions relative to the Amnesty Bill.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>